hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The hole dispersion is 
$$E_h(\mathbf{k})=-E_v(-\mathbf{k})=-E_0+\alpha k_x^2+\beta k_y^2+\gamma k_xk_y.$$
2. The inverse effective-mass tensor is 
$$(M_{h,ij}^*)^{-1}=\frac1{\hbar^2}\frac{\partial^2E_h}{\partial k_i\partial k_j}
=\frac1{\hbar^2}\begin{pmatrix}2\alpha&\gamma\\\gamma&2\beta\end{pmatrix}.$$
3. Let $A=\begin{pmatrix}2\alpha&\gamma\\\gamma&2\beta\end{pmatrix}$. Its eigenvalues $\lambda_1,\lambda_2$ satisfy 
$$\det A=(2\alpha)(2\beta)-\gamma^2=4\alpha\beta-\gamma^2,\quad\lambda_1\lambda_2=\det A.$$
Since $1/m_{h,i}^*=\frac1{\hbar^2}\lambda_i$, the product of principal masses is
$$m_{h,1}^*m_{h,2}^*=\frac1{(1/m_{h,1}^*)(1/m_{h,2}^*)}
=\frac1{\bigl(\tfrac1{\hbar^2}\lambda_1\bigr)\bigl(\tfrac1{\hbar^2}\lambda_2\bigr)}
=\frac{\hbar^4}{\lambda_1\lambda_2}
=\frac{\hbar^4}{4\alpha\beta-\gamma^2}.$$
